prompt.en:
**MyVector**
Build all the files with the classes described in the above diagram so that the provided code (main.cpp) compiles and outputs the expected result.

**Observations:**
- You can use std containers
- You will need to deduce the constructors (if any) for each class by looking into the main.cpp provided

**UML:**
Classes: MyVector, Procesator, <Interface>Procesator, Suma, Find. MyVector has members: Data (private), processors (private). MyVector methods: + process, + clear, + operator+=(...), + operator int, + operator unsigned int. Procesator is an interface with method: + Run(int*, int count). Suma and Find inherit from Procesator.

**main():**
```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include "MyVector.h"
#include "Suma.h"
#include "Find.h"

int main()
{
MyVector m;
((((((m += 1) += 2) += 3) += new Suma()) += 4) += 2);
m += new Find([](int i) { return i == 2; });
std::cout << "Elemente    : " << (int)m << std::endl;
std::cout << "Procesatori : " << (unsigned int)m << std::endl;
m.process();
m.clear();
(((m += {10, 10, 10, 10, 50}) += 2) += new Find([](int i) { return i == 10; })) += 50;
std::cout << "-----------------------" << std::endl;
std::cout << "Elemente    : " << (int)m << std::endl;
std::cout << "Procesatori : " << (unsigned int)m << std::endl;
m.process();
return 0;
}
```

**Expected output:**
```
Elemente    : 5
Procesatori : 2
Suma = 12
Find = 2 elemnts
-----------------------
Elemente    : 7
Procesatori : 3
Suma = 142
Find = 1 elemnts
Find = 4 elemnts
```

